rians such as William Robertson, Edward Gibbon and Leopold Ranke. Accessibly written, a history of histories and historians, the book will be of interest to students and researchers of crusading history from sixth form to postgraduate level and beyond and to cultural historians of the use of the past and of medievalism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCrusadesxHistoriography. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aReformation controversialists.  aRenaissance humanists.  acrusades.  aempathy.  amaterialist reductionism.  amilitary world war.  amodern events.  apolitics.  areligion.  awestern nations.1 aTyerman, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779900540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847799005423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847799005/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles